                            <h2>Costs</h2>
                            <p>Rather than charging huge upfront costs or a percentage of any rental income earned. Rent Direct has decided upon a new style of charging. One which offers full transparency and much better value to our clients.</p>
                            <p>For each property you want to list on the site, you will be charged £20.00 per month. This charge is only applicable while your property is listed. Meaning, should you rent your home in the first month, there will be no further charge. You will continue to have full access to all the tools and functionality of the site. Allowing you to utilise your Rent Direct dashboard to manage many aspects of your tenant / landlord interactions.</p>
                            <p>There are upgrade options if you wish to have prime placement of your listing i.e.. <b>HEADLINER, PREMIUM</b> (front page) or <b>FEATURED </b>(top of search results). These upgrade options carry an additional monthly charge. However. the standard listing includes photo upload, video, brochures, EPC certificates, street views, maps, descriptions and other features as standard*<br /><b> *(fair play policy in place. i.e.. don't try to add 1000 photos etc).</b></p>
                            <p>Additional services such as tenant credit checks are charged separately at highly discounted rates. </p>
                            <p>For all the functionality included in your individual account dashboard, including detailed statistics, instant messaging, historical data, and access to the rate / report and check database, there is no charge at all.</p>
                            <p><b>Tenants costs?</b> None, simply register for an account and have access to the full functionality and features of the site. To search for a property, you don't even need to set up an account.</p>
                            <h2>But what about ongoing costs, and commitments?</h2>
                            <p>Quite simply there are none. Your contact is between the landlord / tenant not Rent Direct. You will have contractual commitments within any agreements you have with them such as paying rent. But as far as Rent Direct is involved we are simply a very, very, very advanced search portal built just for you.</p>
                            <blockquote>rent Direct: No Agents - No Hassles</blockquote>
